text.tspan: MapServer is an Open Source platform for publishing
spatial data and interactive mapping applications to
the web. Originally developed in the mid-1990’s at the
University of Minnesota, MapServer is released under
an MIT-style license, and runs on all major platforms.
It is written in C and it is maintained by a growing
number of developers from around the world.
It is supported by a diverse group of organizations
that fund enhancements and maintenance, and
administered within OSGeo by the MapServer Project
Steering Committee made up of developers and other
Feature labeling also label collision mediation
TrueType font support for labeling and symbolization
Map element automation (scalebar, reference map, legend)
Thematic mapping based on logical/regular expressions
Renderer support with drivers for AGG, Cairo and others
Special provisioning for tiled output generation
Identify features by attributes, point, bounding
box or geometry across one or more layers
CGI/FastCGI, PHP, Python, Perl, Ruby, Java, .NET
Multiple raster and vector data formats
MapServer is used by commercial company, research
institute and public administration to provide maps,
specially trought internet using OGC standard.
MapServer is used also as backend of complete
Consortium (OGC) standards and it is also INSPIRE
